PART: Budget Tracker
NAME: Budget Tracker
STATUS: draft

DATA: Budget Categories
MARKER: budget_categories
INTENT: holds all budget categories and their balances
TAGS: #list
---
The app holds a list of budget categories. Each category has a name, a current balance, and a monthly limit.

STRUCTURE: Home Screen
MARKER: home_screen
INTENT: the main screen showing the overall budget status
TAGS: #list
---
The screen has a header with the app name, a summary of total income and expenses, a list of categories with their balances, and a floating add category button in the bottom right.

WHEN: Add Category
MARKER: add_category
INTENT: user adds a new budget category
TAGS: #form, #list, #user
---
When the user taps the add category button, a form appears. The user fills in the category name and monthly limit. The new category appears in the list with a zero balance.

WHEN: Edit Category
MARKER: edit_category
INTENT: user updates an existing budget category
TAGS: #card, #form, #list, #user
---
When the user taps the edit icon on a category card, a form appears. The user can change the category name and monthly limit. The changes are saved, and the category is updated in the list.

WHEN: Add Expense
MARKER: add_expense
INTENT: user adds a new expense
TAGS: #amount, #form, #list, #user
---
When the user taps the add expense button, a form appears. The user selects a category, enters the amount, and adds a description. The new expense is added to the selected category's balance and displayed in a list of recent expenses.

ASSERT: Category Limits
MARKER: category_limits
INTENT: ensure categories do not exceed their monthly limits
---
A category's balance cannot exceed its monthly limit. If a category's balance reaches its limit, no further expenses can be added to that category until the next month.

SURFACE: Category Card
MARKER: category_card
INTENT: display category information
TAGS: #card
---
Each category card shows the category name, current balance, and monthly limit. The card background color changes to indicate the category's balance status: green for under budget, yellow for nearing limit, and red for over budget.